<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="369" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d369">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.6512/27</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Italian Embassy</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <p>The Arbitration Convention of March 28, 1908 between Italy and the United
                            States was renewed, by an Agreement between the two countries signed on
                            May 28, 1913,<note n="2" xml:id="d369fn2"><ref target="frus1914#pg_388"><hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, 1914, p. 388</ref>.</note>
                            for a period of five years.</p>
                        <p>The Royal Italian Government, in view of the fact that the said period
                            will expire on January 22nd, 1919, would be pleased to renew the
                            Convention again for the duration of five years.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <dateline rendition="#left">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-18">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 18, 1918</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>